{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/path\/init(ellipsein:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path\/init(ellipseIn:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a path as an ellipse within the given rectangle."}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Initializer","role":"symbol","title":"init(ellipseIn:)","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"ellipseIn","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGRect","text":"CGRect","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4PathV9ellipseInACSo6CGRectV_tcfc","remoteSource":{"fileName":"Path.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/Path.swift#L253"},"symbolKind":"init"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"init","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"ellipseIn","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"rect","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGRect","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGRect"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"parameters":[{"name":"rect","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The rectangle that bounds the ellipse."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a convenience function that creates a path of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ellipse. Using this convenience function is more efficient than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"creating a path and adding an ellipse to it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ellipse is approximated by a sequence of Bézier","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"curves. Its center is the midpoint of the rectangle defined by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the rect parameter. If the rectangle is square, then the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ellipse is circular with a radius equal to one-half the width","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(or height) of the rectangle. If the rect parameter specifies a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rectangular shape, then the major and minor axes of the ellipse","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are defined by the width and height of the rectangle.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The ellipse forms a complete subpath of the path—that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is, the ellipse drawing starts with a move-to operation and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ends with a close-subpath operation, with all moves oriented in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the clockwise direction. If you supply an affine transform,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then the constructed Bézier curves that define the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ellipse are transformed before they are added to the path."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Path/init(ellipseIn:)":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"ellipseIn"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGRect","text":"CGRect"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/path\/init(ellipsein:)","abstract":[{"text":"Creates a path as an ellipse within the given rectangle.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","title":"init(ellipseIn:)","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path\/init(ellipseIn:)"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Path":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Path","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The outline of a 2D shape."}],"type":"topic","title":"Path","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/path","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Path","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","type":"topic","title":"OpenSwiftUI","role":"collection"}}}